Description automatically generated" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcbc75ffe-1563-4afb-8a2e-dd1771d48aab_1430x804.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcbc75ffe-1563-4afb-8a2e-dd1771d48aab_1430x804.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcbc75ffe-1563-4afb-8a2e-dd1771d48aab_1430x804.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcbc75ffe-1563-4afb-8a2e-dd1771d48aab_1430x804.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Above: Helicopters are a great way to explore parts of Argentina beyond the ambit of grand, intermittent municipal-region infrastructure initiatives. Our chartered R44 Raven let us hop around rural areas (and even land on a glacier!).</em></figcaption></figure></div><p>In some ways, the reality on the ground was very different from what I&#8217;d expected having read mainstream Western media, <a href="https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2023/08/24/argentina-is-pushing-international-lending-to-its-breaking-point">which has focused on the macrorealities of indebtedness and peso inflation rates</a> and <a href="https://www.economist.com/the-americas/2023/09/07/meet-javier-milei-the-frontrunner-to-be-argentinas-next-president">the question of who will lead Argentina after the coming 22 October election</a>. These are important news cycle milestones, but do not capture (or explain) everything happening.</p><p>As I wrote this blog, the Argentine central bankers (along with the loosest concept of credibility) were <a href="https://www.reuters.com/markets/currencies/argentina-dollar-love-affair-agonizes-over-divorcing-peso-2023-09-05/">stretched to the limit</a> (and international lenders&#8217; patience nearly exhausted) with a claimed quasi-peg at 350 Argentine pesos to 1 U.S. dollar. <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/ARS:CUR?utm_medium=cpc_search&amp;utm_campaign=NB_ENG_DSAXX_DSAXXXXXXXXXX_EVG_XXXX_XXX_COUSA_EN_EN_X_BLOM_GO_SE_XXX_XXXXXXXXXX&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjwpJWoBhA8EiwAHZFzfmoDUQ-TbWCJ-SrGpWwUZ6gIUn08I_Yygi0GqFpx6t6ra-6gcogF3hoCILAQAvD_BwE&amp;gclsrc=aw.ds">The official statistics from 18 September claimed for the running month Monday, August 14 to Saturday, September 13 of 2023 the number of pesos equal to one U.S. dollar in value bounced in a narrow range between 349.08 and 352.28</a> which, if true, is quite a macromanagerial achievement!</p><p>Especially since recent stability has seemingly been achieved simply by buying USD with CNY while selling a modest volume of bonds. Hey, managing an economy&#8211;<em>how hard could it be?</em></p><p>But, <em>if it seems too good to be true, it probably is</em>&#8230; I was able to get around 700 pesos to the dollar at a <em>peri&#243;dicos</em> (newsagent) by <em>calle Florida</em> on September 8, 2023 and my friend Alex&#8217;s family was able to get 720 that same day; that&#8217;s the day I reached out to Noah to write this blog. Exaggerating one&#8217;s currency&#8217;s stability is one thing, but being wrong by a factor of two or more with a straight face is enough to earn a medal (or an honorary policy degree?) in Zimbabwe (Argentina has a publicized rate, <a href="https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/economy/a-guide-to-argentinas-many-exchange-rates.phtml">and then a variety of sector- and purpose-specific rates, plus rates that integrate subsidies or taxes</a>).</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg" width="1456" height="818" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:818,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;A group of people standing outside a store\n\nDescription automatically generated&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="A group of people standing outside a store

Description automatically generated" title="A group of people standing outside a store

Description automatically generated" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F904aed52-b7b6-44f0-832e-3388addedb24_1600x899.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Above: The author (red cap) waits to enter a </em>cueva<em> and get 28,400 pesos for 40 U.S. dollars in Buenos Aires on a day the official, published rate would suggest 14,000 would be the correct number of pesos. Argentines are only allowed to buy dollars at the government rate and this is capped at $200 per month, meaning it is impractical to save in dollars unless you are willing to buy black market dollars from a street changer (</em>arbolito<em>); the spreads are huge and the underground </em>cambio<em> market is only growing. Photo by Brooke Scheck and used with permission.</em></figcaption></figure></div><p>And the tale here isn&#8217;t one of moneychangers hidden in the phonebooth-sized <a href="https://web.udesa.edu.ar/medios/federico-weinschelbaum-argentinas-black-market-pesos-going-dark">backrooms of newsagent stands</a> or <a href="https://finbold.com/jordan-peterson-suggests-its-time-to-scrap-banks-and-use-bitcoin/">speculators fleeing to Bitcoin</a> and U.S. dollars and gold. The tale here is much larger and involves everyday people, prices on chalkboards that have been erased and crossed out and corrected more times than an election-night Fox News infographic, and goods and services being sold at exchange rates meaningfully different from, or even totally alien to, the official story.</p><p>This means Argentina isn&#8217;t just a place of multiple truths and ready arbitrage, it&#8217;s a place in real crisis where the pegs and stories and chewing gum holding things together are all failing.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbfe87595-dcc9-42ed-ab3e-0c64ef33616b_1430x783.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbfe87595-dcc9-42ed-ab3e-0c64ef33616b_1430x783.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbfe87595-dcc9-42ed-ab3e-0c64ef33616b_1430x783.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbfe87595-dcc9-42ed-ab3e-0c64ef33616b_1430x783.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbfe87595-dcc9-42ed-ab3e-0c64ef33616b_1430x783.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbfe87595-dcc9-42ed-ab3e-0c64ef33616b_1430x783.jpeg" width="1430" height="783" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/bfe87595-dcc9-42ed-ab3e-0c64ef33616b_1430x783.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:783,&quot;width&quot;:1430,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;A room with white curtains and a sign\n\nDescription automatically generated&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="A room with white curtains and a sign

