Description automatically generated" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F638e451a-d644-48fc-99a9-52ff9a372f10_1600x900.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F638e451a-d644-48fc-99a9-52ff9a372f10_1600x900.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F638e451a-d644-48fc-99a9-52ff9a372f10_1600x900.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F638e451a-d644-48fc-99a9-52ff9a372f10_1600x900.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Above: The author and his girlfriend attend River (Rio de la Plata) v. Arsenal, a f&#250;tbol game in Buenos Aires on 17 September; the seller demanded dollars in exchange for the tickets to the match. Documents leaked about a year ago after the 2022 World Cup suggested star Argentine players feel the same way, renegotiating peso-denominated player contracts to be dollar-equivalent. Other stars have fled to hard-currency jurisdictions, e.g., speedy juniors striker turned scoring-capable midfielder Juli&#225;n &#193;lvarez still wears light blue, but now makes 64,000 GBP or about 80,000 USD per week playing for Manchester City, versus a fixed contract for less money (in dollar terms) and denominated in volatile pesos. Photo by a fellow River fan and used with permission.</em></figcaption></figure></div><p>How bad is the situation with the peso today?</p><p>I reached out to an old friend in London who is a hotshot at a brand-name white-shoe law firm and represents celebrities and sportsmen, from soccer (er&#8230; f&#250;tbol&#8230;) stars to Formula 1 folks. I asked him what the considerations would be if he were asked to negotiate for a footballer a contract that stated compensation nominally in Argentine pesos. His answer was simple: failing to advise against this would be foolhardy and might even rise to the level of malpractice. I agree.</p><p>After accumulating enormous wealth (<a href="https://www.dw.com/en/https-enwikipediaorg-wiki-economichistoryofargentina/a-54310145">hence the expression &#8220;rich as an Argentine&#8221;</a>) and weathering the (nearly) global depression of the 1930s, Argentina suffered enormous instability in the postwar period, substantially overestimating the size and heterogeneity of its domestic production capabilities and implementing <a href="https://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1057/9780230595682_10.pdf">an ambitious-but-doomed policy of import substitution while marching toward the Per&#243;nesque mirage of quasi-isolationist self-sufficiency</a>.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faa1df68e-037f-4ab1-895d-77290ae8497d_639x1137.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.